        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 11 at 2:26PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 226 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 11
miles north of Purcell, or 27 miles north of Greeley, moving east at
15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Briggsdale.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
